# Environment Configuration for Admin Dashboard

## File: .env.local (create this in fe-stepupshoes root)

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api

# App Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME=StepUp Shoes Admin
```

## Notes

1. Replace `localhost:8080` with your actual backend server address if different
2. Make sure CORS is enabled on the backend for your frontend domain
3. The API base URL should point to the root API path (without /v1)

## Example for different environments

### Development
```env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
```

### Production
```env
VITE_API_URL=https://api.stepupshoes.com/api
```

## Backend Security Config

Make sure your backend `AdminSecurityConfig.java` is properly configured:

```java
.requestMatchers("/api/v1/admin/**").hasAuthority("admin")
```

All admin endpoints require:
1. Valid JWT token in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
2. User must have "admin" role/authority
3. CORS must be enabled for the frontend domain
